                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Galveston</placeName>\n                <date>Feby 21st 1867</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your favor <date>11th</date> Inst together with Power of\n                Attorney<lb/> is recd and I hasten to comply with your request.<lb/> Enclosed you\n                will find sight draft on New<lb/> York payable to yourself for $1896 00/100 of this\n                amount<lb/> $16 is for subscription to the Occident which<lb/> you will please mail\n                to <persName>M Koppel</persName>. <persName>I. C. Levy</persName><lb/>\n                <persName>I. W. Frank</persName> and myself all <placeName>Galveston\n                    Texas</placeName>.<lb/> I was much <sic>disapointed</sic> in not procuring<lb/>\n                you more subscribers, the fact is a Co religion<lb/>ist here engaged in the book\n                business induced<lb/> those I calculated upon to subscribe for the<lb/> Messenger,\n                and I could not prevail upon them<lb/> to encourage you also, in your laudable\n                work<lb/> And it was useless to urge them to subscribe<lb/> to your other works, as\n                nearly all here are<lb/> Germans, besides not religiously inclined.<lb/> Besides we\n                have no synagogue here yet.<lb/> Should it however be in my power here after<lb/> to\n                increase the list of names. It will afford<lb/> me pleasure to do so. I was pleased\n                to<lb/> learn that your health had improved.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32v2cs77/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
